<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="74" type="diagnosis of the new species">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="74">Diagnosis of the new species.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="74">
The new species shows several of the characteristics already defined for the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Euscorpiidae" genus="Alloscorpiops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Alloscorpiops" order="Scorpiones" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Alloscorpiops</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Vachon, M" journalOrPublisher="Paris" pageId="5" pageNumber="78" pagination="143 - 160" title="Essai d'une classification sous-generique des Scorpions du genre Scorpiops Peters, 1861 (Arachnida, Scorpionida, Vaejovidae)." volumeTitle="Bulletin du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle" year="1980">Vachon 1980</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Soleglad, ME" editor="Fet, V" journalOrPublisher="British Arachnological Society, Burnham Beeches, Bucks" pageId="5" pageNumber="78" pagination="25 - 111" title="Phylogeny of the family Euscorpiidae Laurie, 1896 (Scorpiones): a major revision." volumeTitle="Scorpions 2001. In memoriam Gary A. Polis" year="2001">Soleglad and Sissom 2001</bibRefCitation>
). It presents, however, a small size relative to other species of the genus, male 20.9 mm in total length and a very pale yellow coloration. The new species is characterized by the trichobothrial patterns of some 
<normalizedToken originalValue="‘territories’">'territories'</normalizedToken>
or series. Femur with three trichobothria: dorsal, internal and external. Patella with two dorsal, one internal, 14 ventral and only 21 external trichobothria. Chela-hand with an unusual number of 9 ventral trichobothria, two dorsal (Dt, Db), two internal (ib, it), Est, five Et, Esb and three trichobothria in the Eb series. The annular ring is very weakly marked. Pectines with 9-9 teeth and absence of fulcra.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
